	(190,4,'2013-04-22 17:12:41','2013-04-22 17:12:41','Join us on Wednesday June 12 from 6 to 8 PM\r\n\r\nCheck the events page and register.\r\n\r\nIACC-USA is proud to present:\r\n\r\n<strong>World Economic Update</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>John Augustine</strong>\r\nChief Market Strategist\r\nFifth Third Bank\r\n\r\nJohn is the Chief Market Strategist for Fifth Third Bank, specializing in\r\nPortfolio Management for Fifth Third Bank, which has just under $25 billion\r\nin assets under management. Based in Cincinnati, John is a member of the\r\nInvestment Policy Committee and Markets Strategy Team. John is also the\r\nportfolio manager of the International ADR Stock Portfolio and heads the\r\nFunds Management Team. He has been practicing portfolio management\r\nfor over 20 years.\r\nJohn holds the professional designation of Chartered Financial Analyst;\r\nholds a bachelor’s degree from Ohio State University; and is a graduate of\r\nthe Midwest Bankers Association Trust School. He has appeared frequently\r\nin the media – including CNBC and Bloomberg.\r\nPrior to joining Fifth Third in 1998, John was with financial institutions in\r\nColorado and Ohio. He is a former president and board member of the\r\nDayton Society of Financial Analysts; and part-time business professor in\r\nthe graduate school at the University of Dayton.','IACC USA','','inherit','open','open','','145-revision-v1','','','2013-04-22 17:12:41','2013-04-22 17:12:41','',145,'http://iacc.thelodgemediagroup.com/145-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),
	(191,4,'2013-04-22 17:14:40','2013-04-22 17:14:40','Join us on Wednesday June 12 from 6 to 8 PM\r\n\r\nCheck the events page and register.\r\n\r\nIACC-USA is proud to present:\r\n\r\n<strong>World Economic Update</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>John Augustine</strong>\r\nChief Market Strategist\r\nFifth Third Bank\r\n\r\nJohn is the Chief Market Strategist for Fifth Third Bank, specializing in Portfolio Management for Fifth Third Bank, which has just under $25 billion in assets under management. Based in Cincinnati, John is a member of the Investment Policy Committee and Markets Strategy Team. John is also the portfolio manager of the International ADR Stock Portfolio and heads the Funds Management Team. He has been practicing portfolio management for over 20 years.\r\nJohn holds the professional designation of Chartered Financial Analyst; holds a bachelor’s degree from Ohio State University; and is a graduate of the Midwest Bankers Association Trust School. He has appeared frequently in the media – including CNBC and Bloomberg.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Fifth Third in 1998, John was with financial institutions in Colorado and Ohio. He is a former president and board member of the Dayton Society of Financial Analysts; and part-time business professor in the graduate school at the University of Dayton.','IACC USA','','inherit','open','open','','145-revision-v1','','','2013-04-22 17:14:40','2013-04-22 17:14:40','',145,'http://iacc.thelodgemediagroup.com/145-revision-5/',0,'revision','',0),
	(192,1,'2013-03-25 03:14:21','2013-03-25 03:14:21','IACC-USA MISSION:\r\n\r\n<b><i>To serve the needs and growth of Indo American businesses and professionals at local, national and international level</i></b>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIACC-USA strives to provide networking opportunities for business professionals to develop economic, commercial and financial relationships. The Chamber is also involved in business related education as well as advocacy of issues pertinent to business owners. We are a 501(C)(6) not-for-profit organization and was established in the year 2003.\r\n\r\nOBJECTIVE AND GOALS:\r\n\r\n·         Facilitate a network of successful businesses to foster economic, commercial and financial relationships.\r\n\r\n·         Provide source of information to promote bilateral investment opportunity in India and United States.\r\n\r\n·         Promote, encourage sales of goods and services between Indo American business communities.\r\n\r\n·         To serve as a trusted and influential advocate of Indo American businesses at all levels of government.\r\n\r\n<b>How is the Chamber working for the Indo-American community?</b>\r\n\r\n<b>Networking</b> – By providing several opportunities for members to network with each other, thus facilitating the building of business relationships and partnerships\r\n\r\n<b>Marketing</b> – By offering opportunities to businesses to market their products and/or services via sponsorship of Chamber events\r\n\r\n<b>Information Exchange</b> – By inviting successful entrepreneurs to share their experiences and tricks of the trade with Chamber members\r\n\r\n<b>Resource</b> – By providing mentoring opportunities to owners of successful businesses and start-ups, thus facilitating the transfer of knowledge to start, develop and grow businesses.\r\n\r\n<b>Advocacy</b> – By participating in the Council of Chambers of Commerce and by partnering with institutions like the Detroit Regional Chamber and Automation Alley to influence political issues that promote business\r\n\r\n<b>Public Relations</b> – By partnering with other prominent organizations such as India League of America, the Michigan Democratic Caucus, MAI Family Services, provide an avenue to interact with local community members\r\n\r\n<b>Community Service</b> – By participating in group outings to donate time and money to serve local charitable organizations\r\n\r\nAbove all, IACC provides opportunity to interact with other professionals and businesses within the community.\r\n\r\n<b> </b>\r\n\r\n<b>Indo-American Chamber of Commerce Activities include:</b>\r\n\r\n<b>Business After Hours Mixers </b>– Monthly activities, which provide an excellent opportunity to network with other IACC members\r\n\r\n<b>Meet Market meetings – </b>Monthly activities in a small group hosting focused discussions and opportunities to support and collaborate with other IACC members\r\n\r\n<b>Women Empowered – </b>Our newest initiative to support women entrepreneurs and women in leadership to network and support each other and give back to the community of young women\r\n\r\n<b>Business Education Seminars </b>- Provides ongoing seminar presentations and panel discussions on topics and aspects of business ownership and enterprise\r\n\r\n<b>Annual Golf event in August – </b>An opportunity to golf with business partners, building off-site bonds or mingling with other chamber members\r\n\r\n<b>Annual Banquet</b> <b>in November</b> - A forum to salute the success and contributions of the Indo-American community business owners and professionals\r\n\r\n<b>Annual holiday mixer in December - </b>An opportunity to network with friends and build new relationships in a relaxing casual environment\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>FOUNDING BOARD:</b>\r\n\r\n<b>President: </b>Avinash Rachmale<b>\r\nTreasurer: </b>Anil Sakhuja<b>\r\nMembers: </b>Kevin Parikh, Manoj Sachdeva\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<b>2013 EXECUTIVE BOARD:</b>\r\n\r\nExecutive Director: Alka Kudesia\r\nPresident: Monish Verma\r\nTreasurer: Tisa Sherry\r\nMembers: Anis Ahmed, Kasturi Bagchi, Milan Gandhi, Radhika Magoo','About','','inherit','open','open','','17-revision-v1','','','2013-03-25 03:14:21','2013-03-25 03:14:21','',17,'http://iacc.thelodgemediagroup.com/17-revision-6/',0,'revision','',0),
