	(615,4,'2013-03-30 16:04:42','2013-03-30 16:04:42','Our mission is to provide a forum for women to network with other professional women, create mentoring &amp; support opportunities &amp; give back by empowering young women.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nIts goals are:\r\n\r\n<b>1. Networking opportunities with women leaders in the community</b>\r\n\r\n<b>2. Learn about job/career change opportunities and its challenges and rewards </b>\r\n\r\n<b>3. Mentoring/support through break-out sessions, speakers, and open discussions </b>\r\n\r\n<b>4. Young women support through internships, shadowing, and meetings with leaders </b>\r\n\r\n<b> </b>\r\n\r\n<b>Our kickoff on April 17 will focus on the topic of Networking – Techniques and Expectations. Our speakers are</b>\r\n\r\n<b> </b>\r\n\r\nTerry Bean, Executive Director at 313Dlove, CEO at uNetworked,\r\nFounder at Motor City Connect, Author, Speaker, Connector\r\n\r\nLizabeth Ardisana, Co-founder, Principal and CEO – ASG Renaissance\r\n\r\nDenise M. Kiepper, Senior VP, Senior HR Business Partner – Fifth Third\r\n\r\nJennifer L. Cherry, Senior VP and CDO – Marx Layne &amp; Co.','Women Empowered','','inherit','open','open','','84-revision-v1','','','2013-03-30 16:04:42','2013-03-30 16:04:42','',84,'http://iacc.thelodgemediagroup.com/84-revision-2/',0,'revision','',0),
	(616,4,'2013-04-23 03:09:19','2013-04-23 03:09:19','<em>Our mission is to provide a forum for women to network with other professional women, create mentoring &amp; support opportunities &amp; give back by empowering young women.</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOur goals are:\r\n\r\n<b>1. Creating a powerful network through Women Empowered (WE)</b>\r\n\r\n<b>2. Building relationships with corporations facilitated through WE member</b>\r\n\r\n<b>3. Mentoring/coaching through break-out sessions, speakers, and open discussions </b>\r\n\r\n<b>4. Young women empowerment through internships, shadowing, mentoring and scholarships</b>\r\n\r\n<b> </b>\r\n\r\n<b>Our kickoff on April 17 , 2013 - \"Leveraging Yourself in a Networked Society\".\r\nOur speakers are:</b><b> </b>\r\n\r\nTerry Bean, Executive Director at 313Dlove, CEO at uNetworked,\r\nFounder at Motor City Connect, Author, Speaker, Connector\r\n\r\nLaurie Bradley, President – ASG Renaissance\r\n\r\nDenise M. Kiepper, Senior VP, Senior HR Business Partner – Fifth Third\r\n\r\nJennifer L. Cherry, Senior VP and CDO – Marx Layne &amp; Co.','Women Empowered','','inherit','open','open','','84-revision-v1','','','2013-04-23 03:09:19','2013-04-23 03:09:19','',84,'http://iacc.thelodgemediagroup.com/84-revision-3/',0,'revision','',0),
	(617,4,'2013-04-23 03:12:37','2013-04-23 03:12:37','<em>Our mission is to provide a forum for women to network with other professional women, create mentoring &amp; support opportunities &amp; give back by empowering young women.</em>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nOur goals are:\r\n\r\n<b>1. Creating a powerful network through Women Empowered (WE)</b>\r\n\r\n<b>2. Building relationships with corporations facilitated through WE member</b>\r\n\r\n<b>3. Mentoring/coaching through break-out sessions, speakers, and open discussions </b>\r\n\r\n<b>4. Young women empowerment through internships, shadowing, mentoring and scholarships</b>\r\n\r\n<b> </b>\r\n\r\n<b>Our kickoff on April 17 , 2013 - \"Leveraging Yourself in a Networked Society\".\r\nOur speakers are:</b><b> </b>\r\n\r\nKickoff by Terry Bean, Executive Director at 313Dlove, CEO at uNetworked,\r\nFounder at Motor City Connect, Author, Speaker, Connector\r\n\r\nPanel discussion by:\r\nDenise M. Kiepper, Senior VP, Senior HR Business Partner – Fifth Third\r\nLaurie Bradley, President – ASG Renaissance\r\nJennifer L. Cherry, Senior VP and CDO – Marx Layne &amp; Co.\r\n\r\n--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------\r\n\r\n<strong>Denise M. Kiepper</strong>, SPHR, joined Fifth Third Bank Eastern Michigan as Senior Vice President, Human Resources Director in 2009.\r\n\r\nDenise is an energetic Human Resources Leader with extensive experience in the financial services industry.  While most recently at Peoples State Bank, Denise spent most of her career at Republic Bank driving them to top national rankings on the Fortune Great Place to Work list, ultimately achieving #1 bank in the country.\r\n\r\nAs an expert in cultural transformation, Denise comes to us at an opportune time as Fifth Third Bank embarks on our One Bank strategy.  Her combination of strategic business partner skills and creative employee engagement leadership will serve Fifth Third well in the challenging times ahead as we strive to become the employer of choice among all industries in Southeast Michigan.  Currently, she is proud to lead Fifth Third Eastern Michigan at a ratio of 12 engaged employees to 1 unengaged employees.  This ratio is considered greater than the industry average by Gallup.\r\n\r\n<strong>Laurie Bradley</strong> is the president of ASG Renaissance responsible for Corporate strategy and Business Development. This includes the design and delivery of human capital solutions and the development of partnerships and teaming relationships. Bradley leads the cross functional sales team representing the human capital, consulting and marketing divisions of ASG. Additionally, she represents ASG as the founding member of the Mosaic Advantage an international network of qualified, screened and preeminent minority, woman owned and service disabled veteran business enterprises.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining ASG, Bradley was the president of a North American engineering services organization. This public company focused on the design and delivery of customized engineering services for defense, medical and automotive industries. Prior to this, Bradley was the president of the seventh largest outsourcing financial services firm in the United States. This public company designed and delivered customized financial services software and e-marketing solutions for Fortune 500 clients in the United States and Canada. Her career in talent management and technology outsourcing spans more than 15 years and includes leadership responsibilities for the Canadian operations of the world’s largest staffing services company.\r\n\r\n<strong>Jennifer L. Cherry</strong> is Senior Vice President and Chief Digital Officer, at Marx Layne &amp; Co., a Farmington Hills, Michigan-based full service marketing, public relations and digital media relations agency with a global reach.\r\n\r\nA strong background in media relations and customer service, Cherry leads Marx Layne’s digital and social media division, which includes clients across a broad range of industry sectors such as automotive, retail, restaurant and hospitality, nonprofit, real estate, professional services, and emerging technologies.\r\n\r\nShe is responsible for developing a unified brand voice across online and offline media channels, managing clients’ online reputations, crafting online and video content, creating and managing interactive communities, and designing traditional and mobile websites.\r\n\r\nShe writes a near-monthly column for the <em>Detroit News</em> and <em>Detroit Free Press</em> on how job seekers can leverage social media in their job search and a column on social media for the Michigan Retail Association.  She also attends the Detroit Chamber’s Mackinac Policy Conference annually.\r\n\r\nCherry began at Marx Layne following the completion of an internship with the agency.\r\n\r\nFor more than a decade, Cherry has sat on the Regional Board of Destination Imagination, an international organization that teaches creative problem solving to school children. She is a CASL Alumni Affiliate Board of Governors member at the University of Michigan-Dearborn and is a member of The National Council of Jewish Women. She can be found on Twitter (@JLCherry) and many other social media platforms.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','Women Empowered','','inherit','open','open','','84-revision-v1','','','2013-04-23 03:12:37','2013-04-23 03:12:37','',84,'http://iacc.thelodgemediagroup.com/84-revision-4/',0,'revision','',0),
