	(761,4,'2013-04-22 18:59:07','2013-04-22 18:59:07','<strong>The Indo-American Chamber of Commerce (IACC-USA) is a non-profit 501(c)(6) organization serving Greater Detroit and beyond.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>Join us on Wednesday June 12 from 6 to 8 PM at the </strong><strong>Westin Southfield Hotel – </strong><strong>T.C. Linguinis Ballroom\r\n</strong>1500 Town Center, Southfield, MI 48075\r\n248-827-4000\r\n\r\nCheck the events page and register.\r\n\r\nIACC-USA is proud to present:\r\n\r\n<strong>World Economic Update</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong>John Augustine</strong>\r\nChief Market Strategist\r\nFifth Third Bank\r\n\r\nJohn is the Chief Market Strategist for Fifth Third Bank, specializing in Portfolio Management for Fifth Third Bank, which has just under $25 billion in assets under management. Based in Cincinnati, John is a member of the Investment Policy Committee and Markets Strategy Team. John is also the portfolio manager of the International ADR Stock Portfolio and heads the Funds Management Team. He has been practicing portfolio management for over 20 years.\r\nJohn holds the professional designation of Chartered Financial Analyst; holds a bachelor’s degree from Ohio State University; and is a graduate of the Midwest Bankers Association Trust School. He has appeared frequently in the media – including CNBC and Bloomberg.\r\n\r\nPrior to joining Fifth Third in 1998, John was with financial institutions in Colorado and Ohio. He is a former president and board member of the Dayton Society of Financial Analysts; and part-time business professor in the graduate school at the University of Dayton.','IACC USA','','inherit','open','open','','145-revision-v1','','','2013-04-22 18:59:07','2013-04-22 18:59:07','',145,'http://www.iaccusa.org/145-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),
	(762,4,'2013-04-23 16:01:39','2013-04-23 16:01:39','<em>The Meet Market mission is to provide a forum for networking with a small group in a round table setting.\r\n</em>\r\n\r\n<strong>Its goals are:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Make new contacts to lead you to new opportunities</li>\r\n	<li>Show what you know and who you know in a smaller interactive setting to build your credibility and relationships</li>\r\n	<li>Add momentum to your marketing and business growth</li>\r\n	<li>Have fun!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nDifferent topics are presented and discussed.\r\nMonthly meetings are held from 9 AM to 10 AM and are hosted by  Kasturi Bagchi at:\r\n\r\n<strong>Maddin Hauser Wartell Roth &amp; Heller, P.C.</strong>\r\n28400 Northwestern Highway, THIRD FLOOR\r\nSouthfield, Michigan 48034-1839\r\n\r\n<em><strong>The dates for 2013 are:</strong></em>\r\n\r\nJanuary 8, 2013 – Connecting to Meet our Marketing Goals for 2013\r\n\r\nFebruary 5, 2013 – Online Real Estate Auctions – Are they Right for you?\r\n\r\nMarch 5, 2013 - Managing Health Care Benefit Expenses and EEO Insurance Claims\r\n\r\nMay 7, 2013 - The Power of the Pin\r\n\r\nJune 4, 2013\r\n\r\nJuly 9, 2013\r\n\r\nAugust, 6, 2013\r\n\r\nSeptember 10, 2013\r\n\r\nOctober 8, 2013','Meet Market','','inherit','open','open','','81-revision-8','','','2013-04-23 16:01:39','2013-04-23 16:01:39','',81,'http://www.iaccusa.org/81-revision-8/',0,'revision','',0),
