	(811,4,'2013-09-02 17:28:02','2013-09-02 17:28:02','<strong>The Indo-American Chamber of Commerce (IACC-USA) is a non-profit 501(c)(6) organization serving Greater Detroit and beyond.</strong>\r\n\r\n<strong> </strong>Please join us - open to everyone – men and women. Please invite your friends.\r\n\r\n<strong> INDO-AMERICAN CHAMBER OF COMMERCE – USA Women Empowered Event\r\n</strong><b>Discover the Leader in You Through a Sound Body &amp; Mind</b>\r\n\r\n<b>Wednesday, September 18, 2013 6:00 – 8:00 PM\r\n</b>The Westin Southfield Hotel - T.C. Linguinis Ballroom\r\n1500 Town Center, Southfield, MI 48075 - 248-827-4000<b></b>\r\n\r\n<b>6:00 to 6:15  Networking (Hors D\'oeuvre &amp; Soft Drinks – Cash Bar)\r\n</b><b>6:15 to 6:45  Kickoff by Anuja Rajendra, Founder &amp; CEO of BollyFit\r\n</b><b>6:45 to 7:45  Interactive Discussion by Renee Erlich, President of Prosperi Leadership Coaching\r\n</b><b>7:45 to 8:00  General Q&amp;A, Social Mingling</b>\r\n\r\nRSVP via <a href=\"mailto:admin@iaccusa.org\">admin@iaccusa.org</a> by September 15, 2013\r\n\r\n<b>Mindfulness In Motion\r\n</b><em>Anuja Rajendra is the founder and CEO of BollyFit®, a global wellness movement that draws together a richly diverse and inclusive community. Participants enjoy mindfulness in motion while embracing fitness, fun and illumination from within.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>As a dynamic speaker and thought leader, Anuja’s magnetism awakens audiences out of complacent listening and into fully present, engaged participation. The combination of energetic, unselfconscious movement on the outside and calm, centered self-awareness on the inside renewed her joyful spirit, and is what motivates her today to get people moving as she grows BollyFit’s mindful and supportive community.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>As a member of the Michigan Governor’s Council on Physical Fitness, Health and Sports, Anuja passionately advocates for healthy and happy living, uplifting citizens while bringing down obesity rates.\r\n</em><em id=\"__mceDel\"><b>Visit her website:  <a href=\"http://www.bollyfit.com\">http://www.bollyfit.com</a></b></em>\r\n\r\n<b>Finding Clarity\r\n</b><em id=\"__mceDel\">Renee Erlich is an entrepreneur, founder of two multi-million dollar businesses and a certified professional coach. In 2011, Renee launched Prosperi Leadership Coaching, an executive coaching practice working one on one with successful leaders helping them define, plan and achieve their goals.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Renee is a mom to three awesome children and is married to her best friend, Craig.</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Renee is one of Crain’s Detroit Business’s “40 Under 40” award recipients. She served as the first woman on the board of the Detroit chapter of EO, the Entrepreneurs Organization and she is extremely active in a variety of community boards, committees, and professional organizations, including the International Coach Federation. </em>\r\n\r\n<em>Finding CLARITY will be the topic of her interactive discussion.  Renee will help us discover our Values, Purpose, Rules for Living and Rhythm.\r\n</em><em id=\"__mceDel\"><b>Visit her website: <a href=\"http://www.prosperigroup.com/\">http://www.prosperigroup.com</a></b></em>','IACC USA','','inherit','open','open','','145-revision-v1','','','2013-09-02 17:28:02','2013-09-02 17:28:02','',145,'http://www.iaccusa.org/145-revision-14/',0,'revision','',0),
	(812,4,'2013-09-24 01:33:11','2013-09-24 01:33:11','<strong>The Indo-American Chamber of Commerce (IACC-USA) is a non-profit 501(c)(6) organization serving Greater Detroit and beyond.</strong>\r\n\r\nWe are thrilled to offer 2 events on Wednesday October 16 4 PM to 6 PM, 6 PM to 8 PM – at the Southfield Westin!\r\n\r\nDetails will follow…\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li><b>4 PM to 6 PM</b> – Indian Trade Mission Delegation – A chance to meet with each of the delegates and to explore what opportunities lie in doing business in India.</li>\r\n	<li><b>6 PM to 8 PM</b> – Understanding the Health Reform\r\n<ol>\r\n	<li>Rick Notter, Director, IBU Customer Acquisition and Retention of BCBS of Michigan to give the insurance company perspective</li>\r\n	<li><b></b><b>Nancy Schlichting, CEO Henry Ford Health System – Keynote Speaker</b></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n</li>\r\n</ol>\r\nPlease hold the date, noting the times of the two events.\r\nMore to follow – please share with anyone who might be interested.\r\n\r\nRSVP via <a href=\"mailto:admin@iaccusa.org\">admin@iaccusa.org</a> by October 14, 2013\r\n\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><em><strong>Note: Annual Banquet is on November 13, 2013 - Keynote Speaker: </strong></em></span>\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><em><strong>John Fikany</strong></em></span>\r\n<span style=\"color: #ff0000;\"><em><strong>Vice President, U.S. Commercial Sector at Microsoft</strong></em></span>\r\n\r\n<b> </b>','IACC USA','','inherit','open','open','','145-revision-v1','','','2013-09-24 01:33:11','2013-09-24 01:33:11','',145,'http://www.iaccusa.org/145-revision-15/',0,'revision','',0),
