	(835,4,'2013-09-02 17:39:58','2013-09-02 17:39:58','<em>The Meet Market mission is to provide a forum for networking with a small group in a round table setting.\r\n</em>\r\n\r\n<strong>Its goals are:</strong>\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>Make new contacts to lead you to new opportunities</li>\r\n	<li>Show what you know and who you know in a smaller interactive setting to build your credibility and relationships</li>\r\n	<li>Add momentum to your marketing and business growth</li>\r\n	<li>Have fun!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nDifferent topics are presented and discussed.\r\nMonthly meetings are held from 9 AM to 10 AM and are hosted by  Kasturi Bagchi at:\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\" align=\"center\"><b>Honigman Miller Schwartz and Cohn LLP\r\n</b><b>39400 Woodward Avenue, Suite 101\r\n</b><b>Bloomfield Hills, MI 48304-5151</b></p>\r\n<em><strong>The dates for 2013 are:</strong></em>\r\n\r\nJanuary 8, 2013 – Connecting to Meet our Marketing Goals for 2013\r\n\r\nFebruary 5, 2013 – Online Real Estate Auctions – Are they Right for you?\r\n\r\nMarch 5, 2013 - Managing Health Care Benefit Expenses and EEO Insurance Claims\r\n\r\nMay 7, 2013 - The Power of the Pin\r\n\r\nJuly 9, 2013 - Connecting governmental, business and nonprofit leaders in India and America\r\n\r\nAugust, 6, 2013 - City of Detroit Files for Bankruptcy: How This Impacts You and Your Clients\r\n\r\nSeptember 10, 2013 - Cyber Security and Information Security: Are You and Your Customers Safe From Hackers?\r\n\r\nOctober 8, 2013','Meet Market','','inherit','open','open','','81-revision-10','','','2013-09-02 17:39:58','2013-09-02 17:39:58','',81,'http://www.iaccusa.org/81-revision-10/',0,'revision','',0),
	(839,4,'2013-10-18 02:29:43','2013-10-18 02:29:43','<strong>The Indo-American Chamber of Commerce (IACC-USA) is a non-profit 501(c)(6) organization serving Greater Detroit and beyond.</strong>\r\n<p align=\"center\"><b>INDO-AMERICAN CHAMBER OF COMMERCE – USA</b></p>\r\n<p align=\"center\"><b>Cordially Invites You to Our</b></p>\r\n<p align=\"center\"><b>2013 Annual Banquet </b></p>\r\n<p align=\"center\"><strong>Keynote Speaker John Fikany</strong>\r\n<strong> Enterprise Executive at Microsoft</strong>\r\n<strong> Vice President, U.S. Commercial Sector at Microsoft</strong></p>\r\n<p align=\"center\"><b>“Executing Imagination: Turning Creative Fire into Real Results”</b></p>\r\n<p align=\"center\"><b> <a href=\"http://www.iaccusa.org/wp-content/uploads/2013/09/Annual-Banquet-Flyer-11_13_2013.pdf\">Annual Banquet Flyer 11_13_2013</a></b></p>\r\nJohn Fikany is the Microsoft enterprise executive leader for the Heartland Area.\r\n\r\nIn this role, he leads a diverse team of sales, technical, marketing and services professionals supporting all commercial sector enterprise industry accounts in Michigan, Ohio, Kentucky and Tennessee. In addition, he is the Executive Sponsor for multiple national strategic initiatives.\r\n\r\nWith over 24 years of sales and industry leadership, Fikany served as Vice President of Microsoft’s $6.2B U.S. Commercial Sectors Industry practice responsible for driving industry strategy, sales, services, partner and marketing execution for 19 verticals. This organization serviced over 3,600 national commercial customers, in the Manufacturing, Healthcare, Financial Services, Retail, Distribution and Professional Services Sectors. He served on the North American Enterprise Product Group Leadership Team, the US Enterprise Leadership Team, as well as an acting Partner in the company.\r\n\r\nPrior to this role, Fikany was the Vice President responsible for building out the U.S. Manufacturing Industry Sector for Microsoft, including Automotive and Industrial Equipment, High-Tech Manufacturing, CPG, and Oil and Gas that supported 1,100 strategic national enterprise customers and over 1.2 billion in revenue.  Prior to this role, he began his career at Microsoft developing the US Automotive and Industrial Equipment vertical\r\n\r\nAdditionally, Fikany has spent 10 years in the Unisys marketplace and eight years at Oracle Corporation where he served as a Vice President, responsible for marketing, product and application sales, consulting, education and support services.\r\n\r\nAs a native Detroiter, Fikany is dedicated to his hometown. He is passionately engaged in many charity and community organizations.  He is an active Board member of the Detroit Economic Club, Focus: HOPE, Detroit Regional Chamber, and the Boys &amp; Girls Club of Southeastern Michigan. He is a graduate of Central Michigan University, and resides with his family in Bloomfield Hills, Michigan.','IACC USA','','inherit','open','open','','145-revision-v1','','','2013-10-18 02:29:43','2013-10-18 02:29:43','',145,'http://www.iaccusa.org/145-revision-18/',0,'revision','',0),
