	(863,4,'2013-11-18 10:24:56','2013-11-18 10:24:56','<strong>The Indo-American Chamber of Commerce (IACC-USA) is a non-profit 501(c)(6) organization serving Greater Detroit and beyond.</strong>\r\n<p align=\"center\"><b>INDO-AMERICAN CHAMBER OF COMMERCE – USA</b></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"> INDO-AMERICAN CHAMBER OF COMMERCE – USA Holiday Mixer</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><b>Wednesday, December 18, 2013 5:00 – 7:30 PM\r\nChampps Americana\r\n</b>7410 Orchard Lake Road (located in the Gateway Plaza at 14 Mile &amp; Orchard Lake Road)\r\nWest Bloomfield, MI 48322 (248) 538-6333</p>\r\nIACC-USA will provide hors d\'oeuvres; cash bar is available.\r\nThis event is a members only event - if you are not a member, please do so.\r\n\r\n<em id=\"__mceDel\">There is a limited capacity – so please RSVP via <a href=\"mailto:admin@iaccusa.org\">admin@iaccusa.org</a> or 248.882.1623 as soon as possible.</em>\r\n\r\nThis event is sponsored by Anis Ahmed from Northwestern Mutual.\r\n<p align=\"center\"><b> </b></p>','IACC USA','','inherit','open','open','','145-revision-v1','','','2013-11-18 10:24:56','2013-11-18 10:24:56','',145,'http://www.iaccusa.org/145-revision-19/',0,'revision','',0),
	(866,4,'2014-02-18 20:41:26','2014-02-18 20:41:26','<strong>The Indo-American Chamber of Commerce (IACC-USA) is a non-profit 501(c)(6) organization serving Greater Detroit and beyond.</strong>\r\n<p align=\"center\"><b>INDO-AMERICAN CHAMBER OF COMMERCE – USA</b></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><strong><span style=\"color: #888888;\"> Call to Action:</span></strong></p>\r\nGovernor Snyder is on a mission to accelerate Detroit’s recovery through immigration reform. To that end, his team has reached out to our community to learn about what issues we are dealing with first hand. I met with a few members of the team in charge of immigration reform and now I am reaching out to you to collect that information. Our community is minimally represented so this is a great opportunity for us to get our voice heard. Of course, the changes that can occur are mostly limited at the state level. But, issues that are at the federal level are also being collected for the governor to take forward to the president.\r\n\r\nThere are many parts to the challenges immigrants face. For example,\r\n<ul>\r\n	<li>First level is actually coming here. What are the issues that we, our friends or family face(d)?</li>\r\n	<li>Second is once we are here – issues can be finding the resources available to us or the hurdles we need to overcome to become employed such as licensing or work experience in the US.</li>\r\n	<li>Third, if we come here as students, how do we become employed in the US – finding companies who will sponsor our visa?</li>\r\n	<li>Others…</li>\r\n</ul>\r\nIf you have some experience in this arena either because you are a corporation owner who has struggled to get employees here or if you or someone you know has had difficulty with immigration or licensing, we need to bring those details to light. You might be a professional who struggled to get the requirements to employment met.\r\n\r\nPlease document the details and email them to me or call me and I will be happy to document. This is a great opportunity for us to get our voice heard so please do not pass this opportunity.  Also please do include your contact information in case more information is needed.\r\n\r\nInformation is also available on the Internet – here are a few links:\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.detroitchamber.com/january-28-gov-snyder-wants-immigration-reform-to-accelerate-detroits-comeback-city-council-to-hold-hearing-on-arena-district-project-jan-29/\">http://www.detroitchamber.com/january-28-gov-snyder-wants-immigration-reform-to-accelerate-detroits-comeback-city-council-to-hold-hearing-on-arena-district-project-jan-29/</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.nonprofitquarterly.org/policysocial-context/23595-gov-snyder-wants-to-lure-50-000-technically-skilled-immigrants-to-detroit.html\">http://www.nonprofitquarterly.org/policysocial-context/23595-gov-snyder-wants-to-lure-50-000-technically-skilled-immigrants-to-detroit.html</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.npr.org/blogs/itsallpolitics/2014/01/26/265741849/michigan-governor-immigrant-influx-could-jump-start-detroit\">http://www.npr.org/blogs/itsallpolitics/2014/01/26/265741849/michigan-governor-immigrant-influx-could-jump-start-detroit</a>\r\n\r\n<a href=\"http://www.crainsdetroit.com/article/20140126/BLOG015/301269995/gov-snyder-start-u-s-immigration-reform-in-detroit\">http://www.crainsdetroit.com/article/20140126/BLOG015/301269995/gov-snyder-start-u-s-immigration-reform-in-detroit</a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;','IACC USA','','inherit','open','open','','145-revision-v1','','','2014-02-18 20:41:26','2014-02-18 20:41:26','',145,'http://www.iaccusa.org/145-revision-20/',0,'revision','',0),
	(867,4,'2014-03-27 17:33:44','2014-03-27 17:33:44','<strong>The Indo-American Chamber of Commerce (IACC-USA) is a non-profit 501(c)(6) organization serving Greater Detroit and beyond.</strong>\r\n<p align=\"center\"><b>INDO-AMERICAN CHAMBER OF COMMERCE – USA</b></p>\r\n<strong>Networking event - bring a colleague or client and let\'s mingle:</strong>\r\n\r\nIt has been a long winter but it is now time to embrace spring and revitalize!  We invite you to come out of hibernation and awaken your networking skills. Bring a colleague or two, bring a client or two, and let’s plant new connections and tend to our existing ones.\r\n\r\nIn the spirit of new connections, we also are welcoming Sue Mosey of Midtown Inc. to share with us “Revitalization Strategies for Midtown Detroit.” Find out what Whole Foods, Shinola, and The Great Lakes Coffee Roasting Co. already know about the D. Discover development and/or investment opportunities that are available for you and your clients.\r\n\r\nLet’s gets everyone talking.  Join us on Wednesday April 16, 2014 6-8 PM\r\n\r\nPlease join us on <b>Wednesday April 16<sup>th</sup> 6-8 PM</b> at\r\n\r\nThe Westin Southfield Hotel - T.C. Linguinis Ballroom\r\n1500 Town Center, Southfield, MI 48075 - <a href=\"tel:248-827-4000\" target=\"_blank\">248-827-4000</a>','IACC USA','','inherit','open','open','','145-revision-v1','','','2014-03-27 17:33:44','2014-03-27 17:33:44','',145,'http://www.iaccusa.org/145-revision-21/',0,'revision','',0),
