	(1121,855,'2016-04-18 16:44:22','2016-04-18 16:44:22','Details of a fabulous opportunity APACC has for our strategic members. APACC announced in summer of 2015 their partnership with Great Lakes Women’s Business Council (GLWBC) and CEED (Center for Empowerment and Economic Development) to disperse any APACC member up to $50K loan. January 2016, they had their first orientation to educate their members and would like to keep the momentum going with their partners. For more information on eligibility, please click here:<a href=\"http://www.apacc.net/apacc-loan-program\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?hl=en&amp;q=http://www.apacc.net/apacc-loan-program&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1461081941062000&amp;usg=AFQjCNE1w5z0nECTO7VDHveZmh6w813Ddw\">http://www.apacc.net/apacc-loan-program</a>\r\n\r\nAs IACC is a strategic partner of APACC, we highly encourage your members who are business owners (start up or not) to learn more about this loan fund in an effort to  help kick-start their business or grow their existing business. We have orientations the first Tuesday of each month at <span data-term=\"goog_880439662\">8am</span> taking place at GLWBC to answer any questions or concerns they might have. Belinda DuBois, our wonderful loan officer is cc’d in the email and will be conducting these classes each month.\r\n\r\nAttached is the flyer for the next orientation.\r\n\r\nPLEASE SEND RSVP TO VAN NGUYEN - EXECUTIVE DIRECTOR, APACC\r\n\r\n<strong>Van Nguyen\r\n</strong>Executive Director\r\n<em>APACC – Asian Pacific American Chamber of Commerce®</em>\r\nO: <a href=\"tel:248.430.5855\">248.430.5855</a>\r\n<a href=\"mailto:van@apacc.net\">van@apacc.net</a>| <a href=\"http://t/\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?hl=en&amp;q=http://t/&amp;source=gmail&amp;ust=1461081941062000&amp;usg=AFQjCNHyCUghfFP_KuHw-NHrSEFBsTmY-w\">t:</a> <a href=\"http://www.twitter.com/socialmesavvy\" data-saferedirecturl=\"https://www.google.com/url?hl=en&amp;q=http://www.twi